Configuring Field-Level Security:

There are multiple ways from which you can control field-level access inside Salesforce.

Profiles
Permission Set
Page layout
Lightning Record page (Dynamic Form)

We have seen from profiles we can control the field visibility. As making that read only and editable.
Same can be done from the permission set in the object settings for particular user.

Now lets see from page layouts:

With the help of page layout in Salesforce, we can make a field read-only, or required.
We can make field readonly for any particular profile while creating that field as well.

Go to object -> page layouts -> edit -> click on wrench -> you can make it readonly or required.

Even on fields on objects you can set the field level security as
üî≤ Visible	 üî≤ Read-Only to any particular profile

So 2 places to check the field level security:

1. On objects field - If for any profile it is set as readonly or visibility is off.
2. On Page layout - for readonly and required or not.

Why Read-Only Fields Are Editable for System Admins
‚úÖ 1. System Admins Bypass Field-Level Security
The System Administrator profile has ‚ÄúModify All Data‚Äù and ‚ÄúCustomize Application‚Äù permissions.
These permissions allow admins to override field-level security, including read-only settings on page layouts.

So general steps on field are ----------------------

While creating the field I can set:

1. Required on the creation page, whether its necessary or not. If not then i'll leave it. (Once made it required you cannot set it to readonly or not required on page layout).
Also if made required you cannot set the visible or readonly for profiles on the creartion page. It is set to visible for all the profiles by default and can set readonly and both are disabled.

Now once this field is created we can set who can see it or which profiles can see it. 
And once visible we can also set if any profile can just have a read access only (üî≤ Visible	 üî≤ Read-Only). This is the first point to set the read access or visibility.

Now if in future any new profile is created then I can set these things like visibility and readonly access on that profile as well.
Field level security on field creation page and on profile page are interconnected. You can set this security on any page and it works fine.
Both are interconnected. You change on one page and it reflects on the other page.

2. Visible for any profile or not. If visible:
3. Readonly for that profile or not.
