Salesforce Automation Tools:

Workflow Rules: 

What Workflow Rules Are
Definition: Workflow Rules are instructions that tell Salesforce to automatically perform actions when records meet defined criteria.
Purpose: They help reduce manual work by automating repetitive tasks such as notifications, updates, and assignments.
Scope: Can be applied to standard and custom objects.

Key Components: 

Evaluation Criteria
Decide when the rule runs (e.g., when a record is created, edited, or meets certain conditions).
Options include:
Created
Created and every time it‚Äôs edited
Created and edited to meet criteria

Rule Criteria

Logical conditions that determine if the workflow should fire (e.g., Status = 'Closed Won').

Actions

Immediate Actions: Triggered right away (e.g., send an email, update a field).
Time-Dependent Actions: Triggered at a scheduled time after the rule criteria are met (e.g., send a reminder email 7 days later).


Types of Workflow Actions - 

Field Update ‚Üí Automatically change values in fields.
Email Alert ‚Üí Send notifications using templates.
Task Creation ‚Üí Assign tasks to users.
Outbound Message ‚Üí Send data to external systems via SOAP messages.


Example Use Cases
Send an email to the Account Owner when a new high-value Opportunity is created.
Update the Status field to ‚ÄúFollow-Up‚Äù when a Case is reopened.
Create a task for a Sales Rep when a Lead‚Äôs rating changes to ‚ÄúHot.‚Äù

Limits & Transition
Limits: Workflow Rules cannot update related records or perform complex branching logic.
Transition: Salesforce is moving towards Flows and Process Builder for more advanced automation. Workflow Rules are still supported but considered legacy automation

‚úÖ In short: Workflow Rules are simple, rule-based automations in Salesforce that trigger actions when records meet defined criteria. 
They‚Äôre great for straightforward tasks but are being phased out in favor of Flows, which offer more flexibility and power.


You can update any field according to a condition using worklow rules other than Triggers.


Process Builder:

What Process Builder Is
Definition: A visual automation tool that allows admins to build processes using a flowchart‚Äëstyle interface.
Purpose: Automates complex business processes without writing Apex code.
Status: Still supported, but Salesforce recommends migrating to Flows for future‚Äëproof automation.





















